race.comment: The Listed feature has attracted a strong field and you can make a case for why every runner can run well. AIR ASSAULT (1) is the class. He led, controlled and won this race last year and he might be able to do the same again. He brings winning form, having captured the Gawler Cup last start and it was one of his better wins, given he showed versatility by coming from off the speed. He's the horse to beat. SAV ON ICE (4) has been mixing his form this campaign but his best is good enough to win. Any rain in the lead-up or on the day will aid his chances. PROMISES KEPT (6) was solid first-up over 1600m and is a likely improver up to 1800m. He might need one more but he's a top-three chance on his better form. DARKNCONFIDENTIAL (9) is flying and deserves to be considered a chance in this tougher contest, while SIR KINGSFORD (2) looks well placed back in SA and can go close.
